		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>You only have two choices: dwarves and barbarians. Any other race is just too weak, and since a rogue's primary function is to inflict massive amounts of melee dmg, STR is going to give you the biggest advantage. So what race do you like better, dorfs or barbs? The stats are so close that it won't make a huge difference, the extra dex from the dwarf will make your weapons proc a little more and maybe let you hit more. The extra str from a barb will increase your dmg caps and your ATK rating, so it's kinda blurry as to which stat is more important. Oh yeah, and it's a known fact that backstab dmg is directly calculated by your STR (and of course the skill itself), so a high starting str plus some str items (i'm lvl 19 and i have 144 str) will let you do some sick dmg at higher lvls. I have 96 agi and 92 dex, but a friend is gonna give me some +5 dex gauntlets, so i'll have 97 dex, and i figure as long as you have agi and dex around 100, you're good to go, and i don't have to worry about getting too many str items. Oh yeah, and one guy was like, wow i look cool as a dark elf, yeah well you ever heard of the mask of deception? It turns you into a dark elf, and i think it's bard and rogue only. We can also get masks which let us turn into iksars, and something else i can't remember. Anyway, just do yourself a favor and be either a barbarian or a rogue. STR is the most important stat for a rogue, just keep that in mind.<br><br>-- 19th Rogue of Xegony</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</